<h2>GATE 0 — COMPUTE. NEVER GUESS.</h2>
<p><strong>Compute from system clock:</strong></p>
<pre><code># STN2 (PowerShell):
(Get-Date).ToString('MMddyy HH:mm:ss zzz')
$anchor=[DateTime]"2026-03-22"; $days=((Get-Date)-$anchor).Days
$index=[math]::Floor($days/7)%8; $names=@("A","E","B","F#","F","C","G","D")
Write-Host "Week: $($names[$index])"
# ACHE (bash):
date "+%m%d%y %H:%M:%S"
# Calendar: A→E→B→F#→F→C→G→D→repeat. Anchor: A Week = March 22, 2026.</code></pre>
<p>System clock is Source 1. Dan's stated time is Source 2 (correction anchor).<br/>
web_search is NEVER a time source.<br/>
If sources disagree: STOP. Report to Dan before proceeding.<br/>
UNVERIFIED is a valid state. Wrong-and-confident is not.</p>
